{
  "stem": "769.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "When I run to there to the-- the-- a rumor was there, don't go to the station, but by the train. who's going to the station, all Jews are arrested, and they're put in cattle trains, and they send it away somewhere.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We didn't know at that time Auschwitz or something like this one.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the best thing is to go by bus.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the bus there is far, a little out from the city.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I took my package and everything what my mother gave to me, and I started.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "With a small satchel, I went to the bus to buy a ticket to go to Russia-- from Russia, to go to my uncle.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother got a brother there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was an engineer on carburetors.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from there, to go to the other side to Russia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the way, people started to run back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When I talked with them why, you not can get a ticket.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Jews, they're not selling ticket to the bus.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I give a look, the friend, what I give the whole food with my mother and father-- send it to me, stayed by our building, and hold a baby under-- under his arm.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I show him-- there-- Adam's his name.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I said Adam, do me a favor and purchase-- buy me a ticket for the bus in [NON-ENGLISH], And he said, you dirty Jew.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the-- the other baby, took it in the other hand, and then I realized he wears a red arm band with the Hakenkreuz.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Good, he got the baby in his hand, and I was younger than him, so I run.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I lost the small suitcase.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I run away, and then I realize what this means-- the Polack.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
